{
  "id": 5176206485618688,
  "name": "Column wrapping for multicol",
  "summary": "Add support for the `column-wrap` and `column-height` CSS properties, from multicol Level 2. \r\n\r\nhttps://drafts.csswg.org/css-multicol-2/#cwr\r\nhttps://drafts.csswg.org/css-multicol-2/#ch\r\n\r\nThis allows for vertical column layout, or even 2D column layout. Columns can have an explicit constrained height, apart from being derived from the content-box height of the multicol container, and wrap to a new row of columns when all columns have been filled for one row, rather than creating overflowing columns in the inline direction.",
  "markdown_fields": [],
  "blink_components": [
    "Blink>Layout>MultiCol"
  ],
